From MAILER-DAEMON Thu Oct 19 09:15:30 1995
From: richard.gill@fbi.gov
To: cybercrime.taskforce@fbi.gov
Subject: Ellingson Mineral Company - Potential Cyber Threat
Date: Thu, 19 Oct 1995 09:15:30 -0400
Message-ID: <19951019091530.ABCD1234@fbi.gov>

Team,

We've received intelligence about a potential cyber attack on Ellingson Mineral Company. I want all hands on deck for this one.

Jenkins, I need you to liaise with Ellingson's IT department. Moore, start background checks on all Ellingson employees with high-level system access.

This could be big, people. Let's not drop the ball.

Special Agent Richard Gill
FBI Cybercrime Division

From MAILER-DAEMON Fri Oct 20 11:30:22 1995
From: richard.gill@fbi.gov
To: deputy.director@fbi.gov
Subject: Ellingson Situation - Update
Date: Fri, 20 Oct 1995 11:30:22 -0400
Message-ID: <19951020113022.EFGH5678@fbi.gov>

Sir,

The situation at Ellingson is escalating. We've confirmed a breach of their systems, including their Gibson supercomputer.

Initial evidence points to a group of young hackers, but something doesn't add up. I suspect there might be an inside man.

I'm heading to Ellingson HQ now to coordinate our response on-site.

Will update as the situation develops.

Special Agent Richard Gill

From MAILER-DAEMON Sat Oct 21 08:45:15 1995
From: richard.gill@fbi.gov
To: cybercrime.taskforce@fbi.gov
Subject: New Lead - Eugene Belford
Date: Sat, 21 Oct 1995 08:45:15 -0400
Message-ID: <19951021084515.IJKL9012@fbi.gov>

Team,

We have a new person of interest: Eugene Belford, former head of IT security at Ellingson. He resigned abruptly last week and has since disappeared.

I want everything we can find on Belford. Employment history, financial records, known associates. Leave no stone unturned.

This could be the break we've been looking for.

Special Agent Richard Gill

From MAILER-DAEMON Sat Oct 21 23:59:59 1995
From: richard.gill@fbi.gov
To: deputy.director@fbi.gov
Subject: Urgent: TV Hack Incident
Date: Sat, 21 Oct 1995 23:59:59 -0400
Message-ID: <19951021235959.MNOP3456@fbi.gov>

Sir,

A group of hackers just hijacked a major TV station's broadcast. They're claiming that Eugene Belford is behind the Ellingson attack.

This is no longer just a corporate hack. We're dealing with a potential national security threat.

I'm coordinating with local law enforcement to track down these hackers. We need to bring them in for questioning ASAP.

Special Agent Richard Gill

From MAILER-DAEMON Sun Oct 22 10:15:30 1995
From: richard.gill@fbi.gov
To: hr@fbi.gov
Subject: Correction to Personnel File
Date: Sun, 22 Oct 1995 10:15:30 -0400
Message-ID: <19951022101530.QRST7890@fbi.gov>

HR Department,

It has come to my attention that I was erroneously declared deceased in the FBI's personnel system yesterday. I can assure you that I am very much alive.

